<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,870,1185]" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1113]" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">Remarks.</emphasis>
Known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[528,607,1087,1113]" name="Greece" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">Greece</collectingCountry>
and North 
<collectingCountry box="[732,856,1087,1113]" name="Macedonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Helsdingen, P. J. van &amp; IJland, S. &amp; Komnenov, M." box="[871,1128,1087,1113]" pageId="21" pageNumber="249" pagination="5 - 23" refId="ref12727" refString="Helsdingen, P. J. van, IJland, S. &amp; Komnenov, M. (2018) Inventory of the spiders (Araneae) of the border region of northern Greece with Albania and FYR Macedonia. Nieuwsbrief SPINED, 37, 5 - 23." type="journal article" year="2018">
Helsdingen 
<emphasis box="[1007,1062,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, Nentwig 
<emphasis box="[1241,1297,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">et al.</emphasis>
2021). Here we provide new photographs of the male habitus and palp (
<figureCitation box="[811,952,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[223,1356,190,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-17@22.[223,1365,181,1672]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 21A–G. Heriaeus zhalosni, male (A–C) and female (D–G). A, D Habitus, dorsal. B–C Left palp (B ventral, C retrolateral). E–F Epigyne, ventral (E in situ, F macerated). G Vulva, macerated, dorsal. CD—copulatory duct, CO—copulatory opening, Em—embolus, Ho—hood, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S –spermatheca, VTA—ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927077/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">Figs 21A–D</figureCitation>
) and the female habitus, epigyne and vulva (
<figureCitation box="[159,304,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[223,1356,190,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-17@22.[223,1365,181,1672]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 21A–G. Heriaeus zhalosni, male (A–C) and female (D–G). A, D Habitus, dorsal. B–C Left palp (B ventral, C retrolateral). E–F Epigyne, ventral (E in situ, F macerated). G Vulva, macerated, dorsal. CD—copulatory duct, CO—copulatory opening, Em—embolus, Ho—hood, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S –spermatheca, VTA—ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927077/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="249">Figs. 21E–G</figureCitation>
) that correspond well with the ones in the original description of the species.
</paragraph>
